OL,3,CCommons Speaker under pressure after
OL,4,CGaza vote chaos
OL,6,FLabour's amendment ended up passing
OL,7,Funopposed without a formal vote after
OL,8,Fthe Government pulled its
OL,9,Fparticipation.
OL,11,FIt marked the first time the Commons
OL,12,Fformally backed an immediate ceasefire
OL,13,Fin Gaza, though the Government does
OL,14,Fnot have to adopt the position as the
OL,15,Fvote is not binding.
OL,17,FThe SNP were ultimately unable to vote
OL,18,Fon their proposition calling for "an
OL,19,Fimmediate ceasefire", which was meant
OL,20,Fto be the focus of their Opposition
OL,21,FDay.
